		</div></div></div><div class="post-22132 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-writing-life tag-originality-2 tag-the-rules tag-theme-2 tag-writing-life-2 entry"><img width="820" height="380" src="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cards-2617324_19201-820x380.jpg" class="post-image" alt="Learn 5 Ways to Take Risks With Your Writing" srcset="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cards-2617324_19201-820x380.jpg 820w, https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cards-2617324_19201-389x180.jpg 389w" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" /><div class="post-wrap"><div class="post-info"><span class="blue"> <span class="author-img"><img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f6ade23f173b61613026376d4020c416?s=50&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f6ade23f173b61613026376d4020c416?s=100&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' /></span> <span class="date published time" title="2018-03-19T04:00:36+00:00">March 19, 2018</span>  by <span class="author vcard"><span class="fn"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/author/kmweiland/" rel="author">K.M. Weiland &#124; @KMWeiland</a></span></span> <span class="post-comments"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/take-risks-with-your-writing/#comments">42 Comments</a></span>  </span><span class="categories"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/category/writing-life/">Writing Life</a></span></div><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/take-risks-with-your-writing/" rel="bookmark">Learn 5 Ways to Take Risks With Your Writing</a></h2> 
<div class="entry-content"><p>We writers are really kind of a whiny bunch. Our Facebook and Twitter streams, our blogs, sometimes even our books are full of discussions about how hard it is to to be writers. There&#8217;s a lot of (mostly) good-natured woe-is-me-ing; sharing of commiserative quotes from our patrons, St. Hemingway and St. Plath; and so, so much [&hellip;]</p>
</div></div></div><div class="post-22096 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-editing-your-novel tag-characters-2 tag-editing-2 tag-how-to-become-a-writer tag-narrative tag-plot-twists tag-pov tag-setting-2 tag-structure tag-theme-2 tag-word-count tag-worldbuilding entry"><img width="820" height="380" src="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/white-2523978_192012-1-820x380.jpg" class="post-image" alt="How to Spot and Avoid Self-Indulgent Writing:" srcset="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/white-2523978_192012-1-820x380.jpg 820w, https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/white-2523978_192012-1-389x180.jpg 389w" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" /><div class="post-wrap"><div class="post-info"><span class="blue"> <span class="author-img"><img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f6ade23f173b61613026376d4020c416?s=50&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f6ade23f173b61613026376d4020c416?s=100&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' /></span> <span class="date published time" title="2018-03-12T04:20:51+00:00">March 12, 2018</span>  by <span class="author vcard"><span class="fn"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/author/kmweiland/" rel="author">K.M. Weiland &#124; @KMWeiland</a></span></span> <span class="post-comments"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/spot-avoid-self-indulgent-writing/#comments">36 Comments</a></span>  </span><span class="categories"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/category/editing-your-novel/">Editing Your Novel</a></span></div><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/spot-avoid-self-indulgent-writing/" rel="bookmark">How to Spot and Avoid Self-Indulgent Writing</a></h2> 
<div class="entry-content"><p>As writers, we have the opportunity to live lives of creativity, in which we get to craft whole worlds that conform to our every whim. Whether you&#8217;re writing your first book or your thirtieth, it&#8217;s always going to be a heady experience. But this comes with certain inherent pitfalls. Sometimes all this power can go [&hellip;]</p>
</div></div></div><div class="post-22075 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-news entry"><img width="820" height="380" src="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/girl-1721392_1920123-820x380.jpg" class="post-image" alt="" srcset="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/girl-1721392_1920123-820x380.jpg 820w, https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/girl-1721392_1920123-389x180.jpg 389w" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" /><div class="post-wrap"><div class="post-info"><span class="blue"> <span class="author-img"><img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f6ade23f173b61613026376d4020c416?s=50&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f6ade23f173b61613026376d4020c416?s=100&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' /></span> <span class="date published time" title="2018-03-05T04:00:19+00:00">March 5, 2018</span>  by <span class="author vcard"><span class="fn"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/author/kmweiland/" rel="author">K.M. Weiland &#124; @KMWeiland</a></span></span> <span class="post-comments"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/vacation-2018/#comments">14 Comments</a></span>  </span><span class="categories"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/category/news/">News</a></span></div><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.helpingwritersbecomeauthors.com/vacation-2018/" rel="bookmark">4 Fun Things to Read (and Listen to) This Week</a></h2> 
<div class="entry-content"><p>I&#8217;m not doing a regular blog post today, since I&#8217;m spending this week visiting my adorable niece and nephew. Just so you don&#8217;t miss me too much while I&#8217;m gone, here are some goodies to keep you busy! 1. One of My Favorite Posts From the Archives This post from two years ago examines seven important questions [&hellip;]</p>
